OL,3,CMum who took child in pushchair to
OL,4,Criot spared jail
OL,6,FHe said that her role was "minimal and
OL,7,Fperipheral" as she had not been
OL,8,Finvolved in throwing bricks or
OL,9,Fencouraging others to do so.
OL,11,FDaniel Calder, defending, told the
OL,12,Fcourt that Smith had not set out to
OL,13,Fattend the protest on the day, and had
OL,14,Fbeen passing the riot when she
OL,15,F"foolishly" got involved.
OL,17,FHe said that Smith had not expressed
OL,18,Fdiscriminatory views and did not know
OL,19,Fwhat an asylum seeker is.
